{
    "name": "Dire Wolverine",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Dire wolverines tend to be even more territorial than their smaller wolverine cousins, and they defend to the death the areas where they choose to live, often selecting humanoid-settled regions as their own and then fearlessly tearing the settlements apart. Dire wolverines grow to about 12 feet in length and can weigh as much as 2,000 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This terrible wolverine is as large as a bear, its jaws and claws oversized and brutal, its eyes dark and filled with rage.</i>",
